    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1R"/>
            <p rend="align(center)">
                <placeName>Baltimore</placeName>
                <date><sic>septr</sic> 30th 1830</date>
            </p>
            <p>My dear <addressee>Isaac</addressee></p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">When I arrived here <sic>Last</sic> night, I was struck with the<lb/>
                <sic>apperence</sic> of your Aunt and <persName>David</persName> but soon found the
                reason for <sic>there</sic><lb/>
                <sic>Looks</sic> when <persName>David</persName> asked me have you rec<hi rend="sup"
                    >d</hi> my letter I wrote you yesterday, I<lb/> said no, well he told me that he
                informed me about his <persName>uncle Bary Judah</persName><lb/> and that he was "
                no more you will easy know what my feelings might be<lb/> when I expected he had
                only lost his Hand but life also I did not expect, the<lb/> shock was great, but
                good god who can paint or know what misery is<lb/> when told that my poor
                    <persName>Rianah</persName> was unwell and <sic>Quite</sic> out of her<lb/>
                <sic>sinces</sic>, <sic>Laughing</sic> and crying constantly the Doctor says she
                must<lb/> be kept <sic>Quite</sic>. I went up to see her last night,
                    <persName>Isaac</persName> you know<lb/> me, so I have no <sic>accation</sic> to
                tell you, I was <sic>Quite</sic> overcome, poor<lb/> girl it was, no wonder it was
                so, the <persName><hi rend="underline">rev</hi>
                    <add>?</add> Mr Cohen</persName> of <placeName>Richmond</placeName><lb/> instead
                of writing to some body the bad news of her fathers <sic>Death</sic><lb/> Directs
                the letter to <persName>Miss Rianah Judah</persName> on <sic>Reading</sic> it she
                sunk<lb/> down and has ever since been without my knowledge of any thing, sings<lb/>
                <sic>Laughes</sic> and <sic>cryes</sic> in a minute, to <sic>Day</sic> she is a
                little better hope she<lb/> will get over it shortly my dear
                    <persName>Isaac</persName> I am unhappy but gods will I<lb/> shall submit as
                will as I can tell all my friends I wish they may<lb/> all be as happy as I wish
                them to be if you can write to <persName>Isaac Seixas</persName><lb/> let him know
                it but not to <persName>Becky</persName> I am Dear <persName>Isaac</persName> your
                uncle</p>
            <p>and friend <persName role="author">Zalma Rehine</persName></p>
            <p>tell my friends the <persName>Peixottos</persName> that the <sic>preasant</sic> of
                any of the <sic>familia</sic><lb/>
                <del>at my House</del> will <sic>allways</sic> be pleasing to me and your Aunt<lb/>
                at my <sic>Hause</sic></p>
            <p rend="The following is written sideways in the left margin.">all send
                    <sic>there</sic> Love to you and all my friends</p>
            <pb n="2V"/>
            <p rend="align(center)">
                <addressee>Mr Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="align(center)">to the Care of <persName>Mr A. C. Peixotto</persName></p>
            <p rend="align(center)">
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
            </p>
        </body>
